Glossary
========

List of words, with synonyms to avoid and translations:

WORD
def:definition or explanation
ex:EXAMPLE
not:SYNONYMS TO AVOID
.LANGUAGE-CODE:TRANSLATION

--------------------------------------
ADD
.de:hinzufügen
.fr:ajouter

APPEND 
ex:Appending an element at the end of a list.  
.de:anhängen
.fr:ajouter

CANCEL
.de:abbrechen
.fr:annuler

CLEAR
def:To make empty, to empty
ex:clear the position (in the sense of removing all pieces)
not:reset (which in a position means revert to initial state, i.e. the
    starting position)
.de:löschen
.fr:effacer

COUNTERGAMBIT
not:counter-gambit
.de:Gegengambit
.fr:contre-gambit

CUSTOM
.de:ander ??
.fr:

DUMP

ENGINE
.de:Engine ??
.fr:moteur

FILE
def:An object in the file system.  Don't use "file" when "filename" is
    meant. 
.de:Datei
.fr:Fichier

FILENAME
def:The name of a file.  The word "file" refers to the file itself.  The
    orthography in one word is recommended by the GNOME Human Interface
    Guidelines. 
not:file name, file-name
.de:Dateiname
.fr:Nom de fichier

INTERNET CHESS
def:Chess that is played on the internet
ex:To play internet chess
not:ICS (abbr. of Internet Chess Server)
de:Internet-Schach
fr:Échecs en réseau

LOAD
def:To read a file without remembering its name
not:open
de:laden
fr:charger

LOCATION
def:When editing a game, the current point at which the user is seeing
    the position.  Specified by a move number.
ex:the current location in a game
not:position (with always refers to the configuration of pieces on the
    board) 

OK
.fr:valider

OPTION
ex:passing options to a program
not:setting the options via the GUI, cf. settings, preferences

PARSE
def:to interpret a string.  Use only in source.
ex:to parse a FEN string
not:scan

PREFERENCES
def:preferences are global settings.  Many settings are only used as
    preferences, i.e. they can only be set globally.  Always used in the
    plural.  
ex:the notation preferences
.de:Einstellungen
.fr:préférences

REMOVE
not:delete
.de:entfernen
.fr:enlever

RESET
def:to revert to the initial state.  
ex:Resetting a position
not:clear (which would mean removing all pieces from the position) 
.de:Zurücksetzen

SAVE
.fr:sauvegarder
.de:speichern

SCORE
ex:the score of a position
not:evaluation
.de:Bewertung
.fr:score

SETTINGS
def:Something that can be configured via the GUI.  The word is rarely
    used outside source code
ex:Whether the board is turned is a settings
de:Einstellungen
fr:préférences

_VIEW
def:name of an item in the menubar
de:_Ansicht
fr:_Affichage

WRITE
def:to output text.  Used in source.
not:print (reserved for printers)


Pairs of antonyms
=================

open  / close
alloc / free


Capitilization
==============

The Human Iterface Guidelines distinguishes sentence and header
capitalization.  In French and German, Header capitalization is not
used. 



Typography (using Unicode)
==========

Technical quotes are used for filenames etc., other quotes for normal
sentences. 

English:	"technical quote"
		“other quote”

Français :	«citation technique»
		« autre citation »

Deutsch:	»technischs Zitat«
		„anderes Zitat“
		
Apostrophe:   l’apostrophe



Commands
========

EN English:     imperative  Play  
DE Deutsch:     infinitive  Spielen
FR français:    infinitive  Jouer
